{
  "stem": "13141.6",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in the ghetto of Riga, they took my, my father away with other people, what they called the kommando.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But a kommando meant that that was the end.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when the guards came back from the kommando who had taken my father, and my brother-- they saw each other all day long, you know.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And many of those guards were not Germans, but were, were Lithuanians-- Baltic people who volunteered for the German SS, you know?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And some of those, or many of those, were [INAUDIBLE] that the German SS.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They wanted to prove something, you know, to the Germans.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he, he, he had asked that guard what happened to my father.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he said, he was beaten to death.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] My mother was in Stutthof, where my brother was for about four weeks.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My brother-- I'm going back now to '44.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They had arrived in Stutthof from Riga in September '44.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My brother was shipped out in October.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My mother was still there in Stutthof.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was always under the impression, talking to one or two survivors of Stutthof, that my mother-- Stutthof was actually a relatively small concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They only had one oven there, and one gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when I talked to, to my brother about this, he said that, that my mother, when he saw her last, that she was in pretty bad shape.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was in-- that was in September that she was in pretty bad shape.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They hardly had anything to eat.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then when I talked to someone else who was survivor of Stutthof who was there until the very last.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
